    return nanops.nanmean(self.values, skipna=skipna)
  File "C:\Python27\lib\site-packages\pandas\core\nanops.py", line 30, in nanmean
    the_mean = values.sum(axis) / float(values.shape[axis])
TypeError: tuple indices must be integers, not NoneType

The axis parameter is not being handed to nanops.nanmean(), where it is used for indexing.
So I changed (series.py line 650):
return nanops.nanmean(self.values, skipna=skipna)
to:
return nanops.nanmean(self.values, skipna=skipna, axis=axis)
to fix my code.
"
